<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-05-06T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-05-06T18:00:00-05:00" n="357" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d357">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">810.796 Pan American Airways,
                                Inc./413: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-05-06T19:00:00-04:00">May 6, 1929—7
                                    p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>48. Post Office Department requests that you be advised for
                                information of Chilean Government that the Attorney General has
                                approved <pb facs="0694" n="558" xml:id="pg_558"/> the contract
                                awarded to the Pan American-Grace Airways for transporting mails
                                south from Panama Canal to Chile, and that the contract is in effect
                                and operations will begin immediately as far as Mollendo and will be
                                extended to Chile as soon as necessary arrangement is made with the
                                Chilean Government.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Clark</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>